    <section address="Section1">
      <title>Why Ukadc.Diagnostics?</title>
      <content>
        <!-- Uncomment this to create a sub-section outline
        <autoOutline /> -->
        <para>This library has been written by a couple of ADC's (
        
        <externalLink>
			<linkText>Application Development Consultants</linkText>
			<linkUri>http://www.microsoft.com/uk/adc</linkUri>
			<linkTarget>_self</linkTarget>
        </externalLink>
        ) working for Microsoft in the UK. We're
        
        <externalLink>
			<linkText>Morgan Skinner</linkText>
			<linkUri>http://www.morganskinner.com</linkUri>
			<linkAlternateText>Visit Morgan's site</linkAlternateText>
			<linkTarget>_self</linkTarget>
        </externalLink>

		and
		
        <externalLink>
			<linkText>Josh Twist</linkText>
			<linkUri>http://www.thejoyofcode.com</linkUri>
			<linkAlternateText>Visit Josh's site</linkAlternateText>
			<linkTarget>_self</linkTarget>
        </externalLink>
        
        and we've been working on and off on this project for a year or so. The main rationale behind this library is one of extension - we think the 
        facilities available within System.Diagnostics are fantastic but wanted to add on some extra behaviour that we feel would be beneficial. We have two main
        goals for the project - firstly to expound the virtues of System.Diagnostics, and secondly to extend the set of classes to add on some behaviours we
        feel are useful.
        </para>
        <para>That's enough waffle from us - please feel free to delve into the documentation wherever you please, but if you're entirely new to the
        System.Diagnostics namespace may we recommend the <link xlink:href="42a7fe16-f187-4230-ad65-821a1b47ce39"/> section, and if you're a diagnostics 
        ninja then you should try the section on <link xlink:href="427208a7-2b4c-462a-a740-232204b662f5"/>.</para>
        <para>We welcome feedback on this project - please go to the
        
        	<externalLink>
				<linkText>Ukadc.Diagnostics</linkText>
				<linkUri>http://ukadcdiagnostics.codeplex.com</linkUri>
				<linkAlternateText>Click to go online</linkAlternateText>
				<linkTarget>_self</linkTarget>
        	</externalLink>
        	
       	site on Codeplex and feel free to start off a discussion topic.
        
        </para>
      </content>
